**********************************
** Low Level Secuity by Example **
**********************************




1. Install Hex Rays IDA Pro:

	You need to install 32 bit version of libstdc++5

		sudo apt-get install libstdc++5:i386
		
	Not available in standard Ubuntu 12.04 repo's, add Lucid backports (edit /etc/apt/sources.list)

		deb http://be.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ lucid-backports main restricted universe multiverse
		deb-src http://be.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ lucid-backports main restricted universe multiverse



2. References


	"Smashing the Stack for Fun and Profit by Aleph One"
		
		http://insecure.org/stf/smashstack.html

	“Low level Software Security by Example” by Erlingsson, Younan and Piessens
		
		https://courses.cs.washington.edu/courses/cse484/14au/reading/low-level-security-by-example.pdf
